---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import '../../styles/service-page.css';
---

<Layout
  title="Governance · Horus"
  description="Define what AI agents can automate. Every action logged in an append-only audit trail. Compliance-ready out of the box."
>
  <Nav activePage="platform" />

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="hero-scan" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/services" class="sp-back">
        <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
        All services
      </a>
      <div class="cat-eyebrow ey-purple"><span class="dot"></span>Governance</div>
      <h1><span class="hw hw1">Your AI agent</span> <span class="hw hw2">modified</span> <span class="hw hw3">a firewall rule.</span><br><span class="hw hw4">Who authorized it?</span> <em class="hw hw5" style="color:var(--purple);">Can you prove it?</em></h1>
      <p>AI automation without oversight creates liability. Horus gives you granular policy controls over what agents can do automatically, and an append-only audit trail that proves every decision to any auditor.</p>
      <div class="page-hero-ctas">
        <a href="https://app.horusagents.com/login?demo=1" class="btn-gold btn-gold-lg">
          See governance in action
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/HorusAgentsSec/" class="btn-ghost">Self-host free</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="sp-ps">
      <div class="sp-ps-col">
        <div class="sp-ps-label bad">Without governance controls</div>
        <div class="sp-ps-item"><span class="sp-ps-icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E05252" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg></span>An AI agent applies a firewall rule to production. Your SOC2 auditor asks who approved it. You have no record.</div>
        <div class="sp-ps-item"><span class="sp-ps-icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E05252" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg></span>A new Analyst accidentally changes settings they shouldn't have access to. There's no role boundary to stop them.</div>
        <div class="sp-ps-item"><span class="sp-ps-icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E05252" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg></span>You want AI to suggest remediations but not execute them on production. There's no way to configure that boundary.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-ps-col">
        <div class="sp-ps-label good">With Horus Governance</div>
        <div class="sp-ps-item"><span class="sp-ps-icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E8B94A" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span>Every action — user or agent — logged in an append-only audit trail with actor type, timestamp and entity. Exportable for any regulator.</div>
        <div class="sp-ps-item"><span class="sp-ps-icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E8B94A" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span>Admin / Analyst / Viewer RBAC. Dynamic role changes. Analysts can approve AI suggestions. Viewers are read-only.</div>
        <div class="sp-ps-item"><span class="sp-ps-icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E8B94A" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span>Permission policies define what agents can do automatically: suggest_only, approval_required, or auto — per action type and asset tag.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sp-section-hd">
      <div class="slabel sl-gold">How it works</div>
      <h2>Policy. Action. Log. Prove.</h2>
      <p>Define what agents can do. Every action within that boundary is logged. Export the log. Done.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="sp-steps">
      <div class="sp-step">
        <div class="sp-step-n" style="color:var(--purple);">01 / POLICY</div>
        <h3>Define agent boundaries</h3>
        <p>Conditions: asset_tags, is_internal_only, severity_max. Modes: suggest_only / approval_required / auto. Actions: update_library, apply_firewall_rule, rotate_credentials, and more.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-step">
        <div class="sp-step-n" style="color:var(--gold);">02 / RBAC</div>
        <h3>Human roles enforced</h3>
        <p>Admins control everything. Analysts create assets, trigger scans, approve AI suggestions. Viewers read-only. Invite by email. Dynamic role changes. Expiring invite tokens.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-step">
        <div class="sp-step-n" style="color:var(--teal);">03 / AUDIT</div>
        <h3>Every action logged, forever</h3>
        <p>Append-only, org-scoped log. Actor types: user / agent / system. Filter by action, actor, entity. Timeline UI with color-coded tones. Export for regulators.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sp-visual container">
    <div class="sp-visual-label">Audit log · last 24 hours</div>
    <div class="product-mock" style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 32px 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);">
      <div class="mock-titlebar">
        <div class="m-dot" style="background:#E05252;opacity:.7;"></div>
        <div class="m-dot" style="background:#E8B94A;opacity:.7;"></div>
        <div class="m-dot" style="background:#27C2B6;opacity:.7;"></div>
        <div class="mock-tab on">Audit Log</div>
        <div class="mock-tab">Policies</div>
        <div class="mock-tab">Team</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mock-toolbar">
        <span class="mono">48 events · last 24h</span>
        <span class="mono" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.18);">filter: all actors</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mock-row">
        <div class="mock-row-icon" style="background:rgba(224,82,82,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(224,82,82,0.2);">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E05252" stroke-width="2"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:0;">
          <div class="mock-title">finding.ssvc_updated · Incident #44 escalated to ACT</div>
          <div class="mock-meta"><span class="mono">actor: agent</span><span class="mono">entity: finding/cve-2023-46604</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="mock-right"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--muted);">06:31 UTC</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="mock-row">
        <div class="mock-row-icon" style="background:rgba(39,194,182,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(39,194,182,0.2);">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#27C2B6" stroke-width="2"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:0;">
          <div class="mock-title">team.member_invited · viewer@acmecorp.io</div>
          <div class="mock-meta"><span class="mono">actor: user/admin@acmecorp.io</span><span class="mono">role: viewer</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="mock-right"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--muted);">09:14 UTC</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="mock-row">
        <div class="mock-row-icon" style="background:rgba(139,92,246,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.2);">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#8B5CF6" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:0;">
          <div class="mock-title">policy.updated · action:apply_firewall_rule → approval_required</div>
          <div class="mock-meta"><span class="mono">actor: user/admin@acmecorp.io</span><span class="mono">scope: is_production</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="mock-right"><span class="mono" style="color:var(--muted);">11:02 UTC</span></div>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:11px 16px;"><span class="mono" style="color:rgba(122,132,153,0.4);">45 more events · append-only · no deletion possible</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="sp-section-hd">
      <div class="slabel sl-gold">Full capability set</div>
      <h2>Everything in Governance.</h2>
      <p>Permission policies, audit log, RBAC, integrations, executive dashboard and API keys.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feat-grid">
      <div class="feat-card hl-purple">
        <div class="feat-card-icon" style="background:var(--purple-dim);border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.2);">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#8B5CF6" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tag tag-purple">AI control</div>
        <h3>Permission Policies</h3>
        <p>Define what agents can do automatically. Conditions: asset_tags, is_internal_only, severity_max. Modes: suggest_only / approval_required / auto. Admin-only configuration.</p>
        <ul>
          <li class="y">Condition-based scoping</li>
          <li class="y">Suggest / approval-gate / auto modes</li>
          <li class="y">Per-action granularity</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-card-icon" style="background:rgba(122,132,153,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(122,132,153,0.15);">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7A8499" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tag" style="background:rgba(122,132,153,0.10);color:var(--muted);border:1px solid rgba(122,132,153,0.18);">Compliance</div>
        <h3>Audit Log</h3>
        <p>Append-only, org-scoped log. Actor types: user / agent / system. Filter by action, actor, entity. Exportable for regulators.</p>
        <ul>
          <li class="y">Append-only (no deletion)</li>
          <li class="y">Covers team, scans, findings, policies</li>
          <li class="y">Timeline UI + export</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-card-icon" style="background:rgba(44,107,237,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(44,107,237,0.2);">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#6B9FEF" stroke-width="2"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tag tag-lapis">RBAC</div>
        <h3>Team + Roles</h3>
        <p>Invite by email. Admin / Analyst / Viewer RBAC. Analysts create assets, trigger scans, approve AI suggestions. Viewers read-only. Dynamic role changes.</p>
        <ul>
          <li class="y">Email invite + expiring tokens</li>
          <li class="y">Admin / Analyst / Viewer</li>
          <li class="y">Pending invite management</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-card-icon" style="background:rgba(245,158,11,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.2);">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F59E0B" stroke-width="2"><path d="M18 8h1a4 4 0 0 1 0 8h-1"/><path d="M2 8h16v9a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H6a4 4 0 0 1-4-4V8z"/><line x1="6" y1="1" x2="6" y2="4"/><line x1="10" y1="1" x2="10" y2="4"/><line x1="14" y1="1" x2="14" y2="4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tag" style="background:rgba(245,158,11,0.10);color:#F59E0B;border:1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.2);">Alerting</div>
        <h3>Integrations</h3>
        <p>Push findings to where your team already works. Severity-filtered. KEV-active always notifies. False positives never notify.</p>
        <ul>
          <li class="y">Slack severity-filtered summaries</li>
          <li class="y">PagerDuty P1 for SSVC:Act</li>
          <li class="y">OpsGenie critical for SSVC:Act</li>
          <li class="y">Generic webhook (custom POST)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-card-icon" style="background:rgba(39,194,182,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(39,194,182,0.2);">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#27C2B6" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tag tag-teal">KPIs</div>
        <h3>Executive Dashboard</h3>
        <p>Act Now counter, KEV Exposure, Asset Coverage %, MTTR Critical. 11 toggleable widgets. Posture timeline, top risky assets, recent scans.</p>
        <ul>
          <li class="y">SSVC priority grid (2×2)</li>
          <li class="y">Findings trend vs prior week</li>
          <li class="y">MTTR for critical findings</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-card-icon" style="background:rgba(122,132,153,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(122,132,153,0.15);">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7A8499" stroke-width="2"><path d="M21 2l-2 2m-7.61 7.61a5.5 5.5 0 1 1-7.778 7.778 5.5 5.5 0 0 1 7.777-7.777zm0 0L15.5 7.5m0 0l3 3L22 7l-3-3m-3.5 3.5L19 4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tag" style="background:rgba(122,132,153,0.10);color:var(--muted);border:1px solid rgba(122,132,153,0.18);">API access</div>
        <h3>API Keys</h3>
        <p>Programmatic access with scoped API keys. Role-scoped. Revoke without restart. Covered in the audit log. For CI/CD pipelines and automation scripts.</p>
        <ul>
          <li class="y">Role-scoped keys</li>
          <li class="y">Revoke without restart</li>
          <li class="y">Full audit log coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bottom-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Control what AI does.<br>Prove what happened.</h2>
      <p>The demo has a full audit trail, permission policies and RBAC example.</p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="https://app.horusagents.com/login?demo=1" class="btn-gold btn-gold-lg">Open live demo →</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/HorusAgentsSec/" class="btn-ghost">Self-host free</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script>
(function () {
  var reduce = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
  if (!('IntersectionObserver' in window)) return;
  var ph = document.querySelector('.page-hero');
  if (ph) requestAnimationFrame(function () { ph.classList.add('hero-boot'); });
  if (reduce) return;
  var io = new IntersectionObserver(function (e) {
    e.forEach(function (x) { if (x.isIntersecting) { x.target.classList.add('in'); io.unobserve(x.target); } });
  }, { threshold: 0.15 });
  function mark(el) { el.classList.add('reveal'); io.observe(el); }
  document.querySelectorAll('.feat-grid, .sp-steps, .sp-ps, .sp-visual, .bottom-cta').forEach(mark);
})();
</script>
